name: FilFinder results
tagline: Hosts larger images created from the FilFinder output.
body:
# FilFinder_Results Hosts larger images created from the FilFinder output. Currently, this only includes results from the Herschel Gould Belt Survey (preliminary, publicly released data at 350 micro-m). If you have used FilFinder, please consider adding similar figures to the gallery! To add your own figures, create a fork of the [repository](https://github.com/e-koch/FilFinder_Results/). Clone your fork to a local location, add your figures, commit the changes, then push to your fork. Finally, submit a pull request to have it included with the rest of the collection! We hope for this site to contain examples of running FilFinder on a range of datasets, making it easier for members of the community to decide if FilFinder is an appropriate analysis tool for their data.
